<p>Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy said about 55,000 Ukrainian soldiers have been killed since Russia launched its full-scale invasion in February 2022, and added that many people are also officially missing. He shared the estimate in an interview with French public broadcaster France 2.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/Xznvthg_l176JekHVCxoufkIQ0XJjtvbJ3AdJ1PmVTncF3E7yDPzIDNypV9dXRvTrS2xeI33yBRdh9AP4ii2LM3K8quXFmKV9PD52vv6tNi3ZFj4MrCFxL4GKEFW_DNP2AJBPijZRMKHI0IpGU98I8EsF0IIo2PfAMUYpfbu_Kz36xwthmHCIo-Wp6qWeKk' alt='Ukraine’s President Volodymyr Zelenskyy in an Associated Press photo.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>How Zelenskyy framed the figure: He described it as an estimate of Ukrainian soldiers killed on the battlefield.</li><li>Interview scope (Euronews description): In its write-up, Euronews said the France 2 interview ranged from the military situation and diplomatic prospects to the war’s human toll since the February 2022 full-scale invasion.</li><li>Moscow’s stance: Kremlin spokesperson Dmitry Peskov said Russian forces will keep fighting until Kyiv makes what Russia calls the “necessary decisions” to end the war.</li><li>Diplomatic track (as reported by Firstpost): Firstpost said Zelenskyy’s comments came after a second round of talks in the UAE involving Ukraine, Russia and the US, which Kyiv described as “substantive and productive”.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Volodymyr Zelenskyy (Ukraine): In the France 2 interview, Zelenskyy estimated Ukrainian military deaths since the full-scale invasion and said many people are officially missing. (<a href='http://www.euronews.com/2026/02/04/volodymyr-zelenskyy-55000-ukrainian-soldiers-killed-since-full-scale-invasion'>Euronews</a>)</li><li>Kremlin (Russia): Kremlin spokesperson Dmitry Peskov said Russian forces would keep fighting until Ukraine takes what Moscow calls the necessary decisions to end the war. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/2/5/zelenskyy-reveals-55000-ukrainian-soldiers-killed-fighting-against-russia'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li><li>Ukrainian negotiators (talks in UAE): Kyiv said the second round of trilateral talks involving Ukraine, Russia and the US in the UAE was “substantive and productive”. (<a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/zelenskyy-says-at-least-55000-ukrainian-troops-killed-since-start-of-war-13976309.html'>Firstpost</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/fifty-five-thousand-ukrainian-soldiers-killed-on-battlefield-zelenskiy-tells-french-tv'>55,000 Ukrainian soldiers killed on battlefield, Zelensky tells French TV</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='http://www.euronews.com/2026/02/04/volodymyr-zelenskyy-55000-ukrainian-soldiers-killed-since-full-scale-invasion'>Volodymyr Zelenskyy: 55,000 Ukrainian soldiers killed since full-scale invasion</a> - euronews.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/2/5/zelenskyy-reveals-55000-ukrainian-soldiers-killed-fighting-against-russia'>Zelenskyy reveals 55,000 Ukrainian soldiers killed fighting against Russia</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/zelenskyy-says-at-least-55000-ukrainian-troops-killed-since-start-of-war-13976309.html'>Zelenskyy says at least 55,000 Ukrainian troops killed since start of war</a> - firstpost.com</li></ul>